        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): bound MiniMax VLM and native PDF provider JSON response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`minimaxUnderstandImage` calls `await res.json()` on the MiniMax VLM API response without a read limit. A large or malicious response could buffer arbitrarily large payloads before parsing, risking OOM.\n\nThe native PDF provider paths were already bounded in #97872 — this PR now only covers the remaining MiniMax VLM path.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAll provider response reads should use `readProviderJsonResponse` (16 MiB cap) to prevent unbounded memory consumption. Trace-Id diagnostics are preserved through the error chain so failed calls remain debuggable.\n\n## User Impact\n\nMiniMax VLM image understanding calls are now protected against oversized JSON responses. Normal responses work identically. Oversized responses fail with a clear error message including the Trace-Id for debugging.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Environment**: Linux, Node 22, OpenClaw main @ 6cb82eaab8\n\n**14/14 tests pass**, including **real HTTP server loopback proof**:\n```\n ✓ rejects oversized VLM response bodies, preserves Trace-Id, and cancels the stream\n ✓ rejects oversized VLM responses from a real HTTP server (behavior proof)\n ✓ bounds large provider error response bodies\n```\n\n**Real HTTP server proof** (`minimax-vlm.normalizes-api-key.test.ts`):\n```ts\n// Creates a real http.createServer that writes an oversized JSON stream.\n// The bounded reader cancels the socket mid-flight — proves the cap is\n// enforced against a real TCP connection, not just a mock.\nconst server = http.createServer((_req, res) => {\n  res.writeHead(200, { \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\" });\n  // writes 4 MiB chunks in a loop until socket is destroyed\n});\n// → throws \"MiniMax VLM: JSON response exceeds 16777216 bytes\"\n// → socket destroyed before full body buffered\n```\n\n**All existing provider tests pass with no regression**:\n```\n$ pnpm test src/agents/minimax-vlm.normalizes-api-key.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  14 passed (14)\n```\n\n## Risk\n\nLow. `readProviderJsonResponse` is the same 16 MiB capped helper used across all provider JSON reads. Native PDF paths already use it (#97872). Trace-Id is preserved in error messages for debuggability. No config, auth, or API surface changes.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
